The People of the State of Illinois, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Julio Cortes, Defendant-Appellant.(No. 59195;First District (1st Division)April 1, 1974.

GOLDBERG, J., took no part.

James J. Doherty, Public Defender, of Chicago (Thomas Lipscomb and John M. Kalnins, Assistant Public Defenders, of counsel), for appellant.Bernard Carey, State’s Attorney, of Chicago (Kenneth L. Gillis and John M. Cutrone, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel), for the People. PER CURIAM.
